In the 1950’s, estimations of the power required for an EP mission took the following equation for the power per spacecraft mass, P/MS/C,PMS/C=avex2η\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
